{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_queenofspades_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608695/1958012901/0961.xml":{"full_text":"G. 0. P. Fights Move\nTo Curb Debt Increase\nBy 1. A. O\u2019LKABY\nStar Stag Writer\nSenate Republicans are considering a proposal to shorten\nthe duration of an increase In the debt limit in an effort to\nsave the $5 billion figure requested by the administration.\nNo decision has been reached, but if such a compromise\nis deemed advisable, it probably would be to limit the increase\nto this calendar year, so that the new Congress could review\nthe question again In January.\n1959.\nAs passed by the House, the\npending bill raising the debt\nceiling from $275 billion to\nS2BO billion would run until\nJune 30. 1959.\nRepublicans Concerned\nRepublicans are making no\nsecret of the fact they are wor\nried over the move by Chair\nman Byrd of the Senate Pi\nnance Committee to limit the\nincrease to $3 billion as a\nmeans of forcing the Govern\nment to hold down Its spend\ning dgures.\nSenator Martin of Pennsyl\nvania. top-ranking Republican\non the Plninace Committee,\nsaid today. \"Many of us\nfear that Congress will ap\npnprtate more than is in\nthe budget.\" and that revenues\nwill not be as high in 1959 as\nth% administration estimated\nin submitting the budget.\nIf either, or both of these\nfears are borne out. the Treas\nury probably would not be able\nto meet its requirements with\na $3 billion increase in the debt\nceiling. Senator Byrd\u2019s calcu\nlation that a $3 billion Increase\nwould meet present require\nments was based on the ad\nministration's revenue and\nspending figures.\nSenator Byrd agreed that he\nwould have more chance of\nsustaining his $3 billion pro\nposal If it were not for the\nfact that some of the commit\ntee members feel the budget\nmessage overestimated tax col\nlections and underestimated\nexpenditures.\nThe Senate Republican Pol\nicv Committee discussed the\ndebt problem at its weekly\nluncheon yesterday but made\nno effort to put the member\nship on record.\nKnowland Backs Pull Figure\nSenate Republican Leader\nKnow land told reporters he be\nlieves administration spokes\nmen made a substantial case\nfor the $5 billion figure, and\nAirline Strike\nIs Blocked\nFor 60 Days\nPresident Eisenhower has\nblocked for 60 days a threat\nened strike of Eastern Airlines'\npilots by creating an emergency\ninvestigative board\nThe three-member board was\nestablished by executive order\nlast night under provisions of\nthe Railway Labor Act. Its\nmembers were not named.\nThe dispute between the\ncompany and the pilots, said\nthe President, \"threatens sub\nstantially to interrupt Inter\nstate commerce to a degree\nsuch as to deprive a section\nof the country of essential\ntransportation service\" in the\nlutigment of the National Me\ndiation Board.\nSimilar action was taken by\nthe President last week in a\ndispute between Eastern and\nits engineers, who also served\nnotice of intention to strike.\nA spokesman for the Airline\nPilots Association sa'id today\nEastern's pilots voted to strike,\nbut did not set a date.\n2 Who Attempted\nTo Sell Back Film\nSentenced in Theft\nTwo men. who according to\npolice were arrested after they\nattempted to sell a man movie\nfilms that had just been stolen\nfrom him, were sentenced late\nyesterday in Municipal Court\nfor unlawful entry and petty\nlarceny.\nThey are Paul D. Halwtck.\n21, of the 700 block of P street\nN.W.. and John R. Pearson. 23.\nof the 600 block of G street\nN.W.\nEach pleaded guilty in Mu\nnicipal Court to unlawfully\nentering the home of Harshad\nG Mody. 2019 Kalorama road\nN.W., and stealing 8,500 feet of\nmovie film Judge John J. Mal\nloy, following a probation offi\ncer's report, sentenced Halwick\nto pay a 8100 fine or serve 30\ndays in jail and Pearson to\nserve 90 days.\nTkiU/UtCkokt!\nYOU CAN BE SUII V\nWHEN YOU DECORATE\nWITH WINSLOW'S\nQUALITY PAINTS\nBenjamin Moara'g\nGold Bond Valvat\nSamuel Cabot's\nWintlow'g\nVisit Any of These 